>>REGINA: What kind of
trauma cracked her open.

00:25:44.680 --> 00:25:46.930 align:middle line:84%
>>JAWER: --about her pregnancy,
or her mom's pregnancy

00:25:46.930 --> 00:25:47.860 align:middle line:90%
was like with her.

00:25:47.860 --> 00:25:48.670 align:middle line:90%
I would love to know that.

00:25:48.670 --> 00:25:50.087 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Oh, well,
write to them.

00:25:50.087 --> 00:25:52.150 align:middle line:84%
I'm sure they'd be
happy to tell you.

00:25:52.150 --> 00:25:54.130 align:middle line:84%
This was one of my
favorites in the book.

00:25:54.130 --> 00:25:58.570 align:middle line:84%
So a little guy named Jay began
drawing pictures of cellos

00:25:58.570 --> 00:26:00.070 align:middle line:90%
at the age of two.

00:26:00.070 --> 00:26:03.490 align:middle line:84%
And he began playing
by the age of three.

00:26:03.490 --> 00:26:07.330 align:middle line:84%
No parental involvement
nor support,

00:26:07.330 --> 00:26:09.070 align:middle line:90%
they didn't play music.

00:26:09.070 --> 00:26:11.740 align:middle line:84%
He composed five symphonies
by the age of five.

00:26:11.740 --> 00:26:14.590 align:middle line:84%
People are thinking Beethoven
and so forth at this point,

00:26:14.590 --> 00:26:15.970 align:middle line:90%
right?

00:26:15.970 --> 00:26:17.710 align:middle line:84%
Talk about that
kind of phenomenon,

00:26:17.710 --> 00:26:19.990 align:middle line:84%
because I think that
really kind of pulls

00:26:19.990 --> 00:26:22.870 align:middle line:84%
on everybody's imagination
and heartstrings,

00:26:22.870 --> 00:26:27.202 align:middle line:84%
both to see a little person
just emerge with these talents.

00:26:27.202 --> 00:26:29.410 align:middle line:84%
>>JAWER: Yeah, that story
and many others in the book

00:26:29.410 --> 00:26:31.900 align:middle line:84%
come from a guy named
Darold Treffert, who

00:26:31.900 --> 00:26:34.673 align:middle line:84%
is probably the world's
foremost authority on prodigies.

00:26:34.673 --> 00:26:36.340 align:middle line:84%
He was the consultant
on the movie "Rain

00:26:36.340 --> 00:26:39.130 align:middle line:90%
Man" with Dustin Hoffman.

00:26:39.130 --> 00:26:41.560 align:middle line:84%
And Dustin Hoffman,
by the way, played

00:26:41.560 --> 00:26:44.745 align:middle line:84%
a savant, an autistic savant,
not a prodigy, but a savant,

00:26:44.745 --> 00:26:47.920 align:middle line:84%
had this amazing capability
of almost instantaneous

00:26:47.920 --> 00:26:50.150 align:middle line:90%
memorization of everything.

00:26:50.150 --> 00:26:52.150 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: He knew what
the rain was 10 years ago

00:26:52.150 --> 00:26:52.950 align:middle line:90%
on a certain day.

00:26:52.950 --> 00:26:55.870 align:middle line:84%
He knew what the weather
patterns were in a given area.

00:26:55.870 --> 00:26:57.588 align:middle line:84%
It was an insane
amount of knowledge.

00:26:57.588 --> 00:26:59.130 align:middle line:84%
>>JAWER: He was a
calendar calculator

00:26:59.130 --> 00:27:03.887 align:middle line:84%
and he could read things
independently with each eye.

00:27:03.887 --> 00:27:06.220 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Oh, yeah, so obviously
both of the hemispheres

00:27:06.220 --> 00:27:08.137 align:middle line:84%
were firing but independently
from each other.

00:27:08.137 --> 00:27:08.955 align:middle line:90%
Really interesting.

00:27:08.955 --> 00:27:10.580 align:middle line:84%
>>JAWER: His actual
name, the character

00:27:10.580 --> 00:27:12.622 align:middle line:84%
or the person that character
is based on his name

00:27:12.622 --> 00:27:15.160 align:middle line:90%
was named Kim Peek, Kim Peek.

00:27:15.160 --> 00:27:17.890 align:middle line:84%
But, yeah, there
are these instances

00:27:17.890 --> 00:27:20.020 align:middle line:90%
of incredible prodigies.

00:27:20.020 --> 00:27:23.160 align:middle line:84%
It raises many, many questions,
some very profound questions

00:27:23.160 --> 00:27:24.160 align:middle line:90%
about what it is to be--

00:27:24.160 --> 00:27:26.160 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: I'm really
comfortable with the notion

00:27:26.160 --> 00:27:27.650 align:middle line:84%
of continued cycles
of incarnation,

00:27:27.650 --> 00:27:29.110 align:middle line:90%
I think, well, sure.

00:27:29.110 --> 00:27:31.240 align:middle line:84%
You bring that one forward,
it's ready and loaded,

00:27:31.240 --> 00:27:33.400 align:middle line:84%
and all you have to do is
get in a little vehicle

00:27:33.400 --> 00:27:36.140 align:middle line:84%
and get some pencil, and
paper, and an instrument,

00:27:36.140 --> 00:27:39.130 align:middle line:90%
and you're ready to go.

00:27:39.130 --> 00:27:41.440 align:middle line:90%
>>JAWER: Yeah, we seem to be--

00:27:41.440 --> 00:27:45.192 align:middle line:84%
at least some of us have
access to vast potential.

00:27:45.192 --> 00:27:46.900 align:middle line:84%
And the question is--
and Darold Treffert

00:27:46.900 --> 00:27:49.720 align:middle line:84%
asks this is-- does everyone
have a little "Rain Man"

00:27:49.720 --> 00:27:51.190 align:middle line:90%
capacity within them?

00:27:51.190 --> 00:27:52.280 align:middle line:90%
That's an open question.

00:27:52.280 --> 00:27:54.700 align:middle line:84%
I mean people would
answer different ways.

00:27:54.700 --> 00:27:56.830 align:middle line:84%
But I think by looking
at these particular kinds

00:27:56.830 --> 00:28:01.310 align:middle line:84%
of exceptional kids and
other exceptional people,

00:28:01.310 --> 00:28:03.190 align:middle line:84%
we do have a sense
that maybe there

00:28:03.190 --> 00:28:07.930 align:middle line:84%
is a path from
birth and previous

00:28:07.930 --> 00:28:11.020 align:middle line:84%
that there's much more
knowledge and capability

00:28:11.020 --> 00:28:11.998 align:middle line:90%
than we could guess.

00:28:11.998 --> 00:28:13.540 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Oh, I
think that's so true.

00:28:13.540 --> 00:28:16.060 align:middle line:84%
Humans are such an
interesting species.

00:28:16.060 --> 00:28:17.890 align:middle line:90%
This is one named Mariah.

00:28:17.890 --> 00:28:20.230 align:middle line:84%
This was apparent
past-life memory.

00:28:20.230 --> 00:28:22.720 align:middle line:90%
"Mariah was 2 and 1/2 years old.

00:28:22.720 --> 00:28:25.630 align:middle line:84%
She came to her teacher
sobbing, asking her

00:28:25.630 --> 00:28:27.940 align:middle line:90%
to help her find her children."

00:28:27.940 --> 00:28:31.030 align:middle line:84%
And she named the French
village that she was from.

00:28:31.030 --> 00:28:33.250 align:middle line:84%
She described even
her own death.

00:28:33.250 --> 00:28:34.870 align:middle line:84%
Talk about this
case a little bit.

00:28:34.870 --> 00:28:39.370 align:middle line:84%
This is truly amazing as far as
thin walls and sensitivity go.

00:28:39.370 --> 00:28:43.300 align:middle line:84%
>>JAWER: Yes, this comes
from a gifted and talented

00:28:43.300 --> 00:28:47.710 align:middle line:84%
organization and accounts
of these kinds of kids.

00:28:47.710 --> 00:28:54.100 align:middle line:84%
And I believe with
Mariah, she was weeping.

00:28:54.100 --> 00:28:55.960 align:middle line:84%
The teachers were
incredibly moved

00:28:55.960 --> 00:28:58.930 align:middle line:84%
because she cared so
much for these kids,

00:28:58.930 --> 00:29:00.430 align:middle line:84%
and she didn't know
where they were.

00:29:00.430 --> 00:29:01.300 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Her kids.

00:29:01.300 --> 00:29:05.800 align:middle line:84%
>>JAWER: And it seemed to
be an accident on a wagon

00:29:05.800 --> 00:29:07.810 align:middle line:84%
or something like
that, as what I recall,

00:29:07.810 --> 00:29:10.340 align:middle line:90%
or a fire that took place.

00:29:10.340 --> 00:29:12.340 align:middle line:84%
I might be mixing up a
couple of these accounts.

00:29:12.340 --> 00:29:17.710 align:middle line:84%
But it's the emotion to
me that is paramount.

00:29:17.710 --> 00:29:22.120 align:middle line:84%
To her teachers, I remember
them saying it was her emotion.

00:29:22.120 --> 00:29:24.310 align:middle line:84%
It was the way
she cared so much.

00:29:24.310 --> 00:29:25.410 align:middle line:90%
And

00:29:25.410 --> 00:29:27.493 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: It was such a
visceral, real experience.

00:29:27.493 --> 00:29:30.680 align:middle line:84%
>>JAWER: It was such a visceral,
immediate experience for her.

00:29:30.680 --> 00:29:33.620 align:middle line:84%
And that's why I think
emotion is so critical.

00:29:33.620 --> 00:29:36.190 align:middle line:84%
So the subtitle of
"Sensitive Soul"

00:29:36.190 --> 00:29:38.650 align:middle line:84%
is "The Overlooked
Role of Emotion

00:29:38.650 --> 00:29:40.120 align:middle line:90%
in Extraordinary States."

00:29:40.120 --> 00:29:42.610 align:middle line:84%
And that's really what my
work overall is looking at

00:29:42.610 --> 00:29:44.860 align:middle line:90%
is the power of emotion.

00:29:44.860 --> 00:29:48.760 align:middle line:84%
And I believe I go so far as to
suggest that emotion is really

00:29:48.760 --> 00:29:51.910 align:middle line:84%
fundamentally what connects
us with one another,

00:29:51.910 --> 00:29:56.980 align:middle line:84%
with animals, with nature,
with whatever created us.

00:29:56.980 --> 00:30:00.490 align:middle line:84%
I would go so far as to suggest
that we live in a fundamentally

00:30:00.490 --> 00:30:02.050 align:middle line:90%
emotional universe.

00:30:02.050 --> 00:30:03.760 align:middle line:84%
So that these kinds
of experiences,

00:30:03.760 --> 00:30:08.080 align:middle line:84%
which are traumatic,
have a resonance to them.

00:30:08.080 --> 00:30:10.990 align:middle line:84%
And it tends to be
with these kids.

00:30:10.990 --> 00:30:14.530 align:middle line:84%
For example, kids that recount
past lives or someone else's

00:30:14.530 --> 00:30:16.750 align:middle line:90%
life.

00:30:16.750 --> 00:30:19.270 align:middle line:84%
It's been calculated that
of the many cases that

00:30:19.270 --> 00:30:20.350 align:middle line:90%
have been documented--

00:30:20.350 --> 00:30:24.163 align:middle line:84%
Ian Stevenson, you mentioned,
and his successor's

00:30:24.163 --> 00:30:26.080 align:middle line:84%
name Jim Tucker at the
University of Virginia.

00:30:26.080 --> 00:30:28.330 align:middle line:84%
They've done 2,500 cases
or something like this.

00:30:28.330 --> 00:30:31.720 align:middle line:84%
In 70% of them, they
involve some sort

00:30:31.720 --> 00:30:34.690 align:middle line:90%
of traumatic death or demise.

00:30:34.690 --> 00:30:38.037 align:middle line:84%
So it's the trauma and the
huge emotion that's riled up.

00:30:38.037 --> 00:30:40.120 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And it's like
the emotion ties them back

00:30:40.120 --> 00:30:42.880 align:middle line:84%
into that experience,
because those experiences can

00:30:42.880 --> 00:30:45.150 align:middle line:84%
be validated in a
lot of these cases.

00:30:45.150 --> 00:30:47.170 align:middle line:84%
I remember a few of
them, and they're just

00:30:47.170 --> 00:30:50.290 align:middle line:84%
really exceptional
where they go up and say

00:30:50.290 --> 00:30:53.350 align:middle line:84%
that's the house I used to live
in and go knock on the door.

00:30:53.350 --> 00:30:55.840 align:middle line:84%
And their old wife is
there, who's old now.

00:30:55.840 --> 00:30:57.100 align:middle line:90%
They've been dead for a while.

00:30:57.100 --> 00:30:59.860 align:middle line:84%
And they know where
their pipe is.

00:30:59.860 --> 00:31:01.630 align:middle line:84%
>>JAWER: Yes, the
emotion seems to be

00:31:01.630 --> 00:31:04.000 align:middle line:84%
the magnet, the sort
of the glue that

00:31:04.000 --> 00:31:07.390 align:middle line:84%
holds the different details
of that recollection together.

00:31:07.390 --> 00:31:09.190 align:middle line:84%
And that's what I'm
most fascinated with

00:31:09.190 --> 00:31:12.700 align:middle line:84%
is the emotion, because we
all are emotional creatures.

00:31:12.700 --> 00:31:15.370 align:middle line:84%
But I tend to think emotion is
much more profound than it's

00:31:15.370 --> 00:31:16.520 align:middle line:90%
typically given credit.

00:31:16.520 --> 00:31:17.895 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So let
me ask you this.

00:31:17.895 --> 00:31:22.120 align:middle line:84%
So in the case of Mariah looking
for her lost children so upset,

00:31:22.120 --> 00:31:23.980 align:middle line:84%
is that one of those
situations, then,

00:31:23.980 --> 00:31:26.080 align:middle line:84%
if you wanted to look at it this
way that's possible where she--

00:31:26.080 --> 00:31:27.372 align:middle line:90%
and you mentioned this earlier.

00:31:27.372 --> 00:31:28.510 align:middle line:90%
I think you alluded to it--

00:31:28.510 --> 00:31:31.210 align:middle line:84%
that she could also be
tapping into someone else's

00:31:31.210 --> 00:31:35.830 align:middle line:84%
field, someone else's emotions,
someone else's experience even?

00:31:35.830 --> 00:31:38.380 align:middle line:84%
>>JAWER: Yes, that's
entirely possible.

00:31:38.380 --> 00:31:42.235 align:middle line:84%
The term is telesomatic
experiences.

00:31:42.235 --> 00:31:44.560 align:middle line:90%
"Tele" as in distance.

00:31:44.560 --> 00:31:47.650 align:middle line:84%
"Telepathy" literally means
feeling at a distance.

00:31:47.650 --> 00:31:51.700 align:middle line:84%
Telesomatic is where
people actually feel,

00:31:51.700 --> 00:31:57.140 align:middle line:84%
literally, someone else's
pain at a distance.

00:31:57.140 --> 00:31:59.300 align:middle line:84%
So there are accounts of
these in the book as well.

00:31:59.300 --> 00:32:01.240 align:middle line:84%
And I'm sure you
and your viewers

00:32:01.240 --> 00:32:05.197 align:middle line:84%
are familiar with situations
where people feel uneasy.

00:32:05.197 --> 00:32:07.780 align:middle line:84%
Something's happened to someone
that they know and care about,

00:32:07.780 --> 00:32:09.447 align:middle line:84%
they can't quite put
their finger on it,

00:32:09.447 --> 00:32:13.870 align:middle line:84%
or maybe they can and they feel
a headache, or a stomach ache,

00:32:13.870 --> 00:32:17.050 align:middle line:84%
or they have to drop their
pen because their hand is just

00:32:17.050 --> 00:32:18.940 align:middle line:90%
completely pained.

00:32:18.940 --> 00:32:20.200 align:middle line:90%
There are these accounts.

00:32:20.200 --> 00:32:25.990 align:middle line:84%
And so it seems that emotion
can traverse time and distance.

00:32:25.990 --> 00:32:29.280 align:middle line:84%
And these telesomatic
experiences attest to that.

00:32:29.280 --> 00:32:34.150 align:middle line:84%
So it could be that that's
held in common, as you suggest,

00:32:34.150 --> 00:32:38.020 align:middle line:84%
with kids to have these
memories of someone else's life.

00:32:38.020 --> 00:32:40.370 align:middle line:84%
It's something that
happened some other time,

00:32:40.370 --> 00:32:43.015 align:middle line:84%
some other place, not
necessarily a reincarnation,

00:32:43.015 --> 00:32:44.515 align:middle line:84%
but they're picking
up on something.

00:32:44.515 --> 00:32:45.730 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: It could
be, but it may not be.

00:32:45.730 --> 00:32:46.060 align:middle line:90%
>>JAWER: It may be.

00:32:46.060 --> 00:32:46.970 align:middle line:90%
We don't know.

00:32:46.970 --> 00:32:47.770 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK.

00:32:47.770 --> 00:32:49.180 align:middle line:90%
And also ghosts.

00:32:49.180 --> 00:32:51.710 align:middle line:84%
Now you're starting to get over
into poltergeists and ghosts

00:32:51.710 --> 00:32:52.510 align:middle line:90%
as well.

00:32:52.510 --> 00:32:54.385 align:middle line:84%
You have a little
different perception on it.

00:32:54.385 --> 00:32:56.230 align:middle line:84%
And we talk about
Matthew Manning

00:32:56.230 --> 00:32:59.380 align:middle line:84%
because he had a poltergeist
situation with telekinesis.

00:32:59.380 --> 00:33:02.600 align:middle line:90%
Now this one's fascinating.

00:33:02.600 --> 00:33:06.280 align:middle line:84%
I've done some stories on
this phenomena including

00:33:06.280 --> 00:33:09.850 align:middle line:84%
the woman whose family
the movies "The Conjuring"

00:33:09.850 --> 00:33:12.970 align:middle line:84%
was based on and how
crazy it was at that home.

00:33:12.970 --> 00:33:16.930 align:middle line:84%
In Matthew's case, the furniture
would lift off the ground

00:33:16.930 --> 00:33:19.420 align:middle line:84%
and hurdle itself
through the air.

00:33:19.420 --> 00:33:21.820 align:middle line:84%
But then this is the
interesting part-- hundreds

00:33:21.820 --> 00:33:25.420 align:middle line:84%
of dead people's signatures
suddenly appeared on his wall

00:33:25.420 --> 00:33:27.730 align:middle line:90%
all in different handwriting.

00:33:27.730 --> 00:33:30.760 align:middle line:84%
And then he began
automatic writing

00:33:30.760 --> 00:33:32.890 align:middle line:90%
in fluent Chinese and Arabic.

00:33:32.890 --> 00:33:35.160 align:middle line:90%
So tell us about this guy.

00:33:35.160 --> 00:33:37.490 align:middle line:84%
>>JAWER: Yeah, and
he also, later on I

00:33:37.490 --> 00:33:40.820 align:middle line:84%
believe, he was able
to produce artwork

00:33:40.820 --> 00:33:43.670 align:middle line:84%
that was very reminiscent
of different English artists

00:33:43.670 --> 00:33:45.975 align:middle line:84%
from the 17th and
18th centuries.

00:33:45.975 --> 00:33:47.600 align:middle line:84%
So incredible,
incredible capabilities.

00:33:47.600 --> 00:33:48.920 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So this guy's
wide open obviously,

00:33:48.920 --> 00:33:51.540 align:middle line:84%
but what about the poltergeist
and ghost aspect of it?

00:33:51.540 --> 00:33:52.670 align:middle line:84%
Because you have a
few of those in there,

00:33:52.670 --> 00:33:54.000 align:middle line:84%
we just don't have enough
time to go over all of them.

00:33:54.000 --> 00:33:55.920 align:middle line:84%
>>JAWER: Yeah, well
I'll mention something

00:33:55.920 --> 00:33:59.270 align:middle line:84%
that happened with me which
I think is relevant and again

00:33:59.270 --> 00:34:01.880 align:middle line:90%
came out of the blue.

00:34:01.880 --> 00:34:04.430 align:middle line:84%
I remember many years
ago, 20 some years,

00:34:04.430 --> 00:34:07.740 align:middle line:84%
I was late at night and
pacing back and forth.

00:34:07.740 --> 00:34:09.971 align:middle line:84%
And I was concerned and
agitated about something.

00:34:09.971 --> 00:34:11.179 align:middle line:90%
I don't remember what it was.

00:34:11.179 --> 00:34:13.940 align:middle line:84%
But there was a light
bulb in the socket

00:34:13.940 --> 00:34:20.120 align:middle line:84%
that was on the ceiling that
just dropped, just dropped out.

00:34:20.120 --> 00:34:23.159 align:middle line:84%
And that never happened
before, never happened after.

00:34:23.159 --> 00:34:25.760 align:middle line:84%
And the convergence
of the conjunction

00:34:25.760 --> 00:34:30.420 align:middle line:84%
with me being riled up got
me to thinking about this.

00:34:30.420 --> 00:34:34.040 align:middle line:84%
So again, I think that with
a poltergeist, phenomena

00:34:34.040 --> 00:34:36.920 align:middle line:84%
and apparitions as
well, in general ghosts,

00:34:36.920 --> 00:34:42.199 align:middle line:84%
I think that there are
feelings that somehow emanate

00:34:42.199 --> 00:34:44.780 align:middle line:84%
from someone, whether
that person is there

00:34:44.780 --> 00:34:46.940 align:middle line:84%
at that moment in that
particular location

00:34:46.940 --> 00:34:49.030 align:middle line:84%
or maybe they were
there some time before.

00:34:49.030 --> 00:34:49.830 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:34:49.830 --> 00:34:51.659 align:middle line:84%
And they're
electrically charged.

00:34:51.659 --> 00:34:53.560 align:middle line:84%
I mean the emotions
have a charge to them.

00:34:53.560 --> 00:34:55.909 align:middle line:84%
>>JAWER: We talk
about them that way--

00:34:55.909 --> 00:34:57.260 align:middle line:90%
this feeling is electric.

00:34:57.260 --> 00:34:58.340 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah, exactly.

00:34:58.340 --> 00:35:00.170 align:middle line:90%
Well in that situation too--

00:35:00.170 --> 00:35:02.930 align:middle line:84%
referring back to
Andrea Perron's book--

00:35:02.930 --> 00:35:05.240 align:middle line:84%
she said when these poltergeist
activities occurred--

00:35:05.240 --> 00:35:08.060 align:middle line:84%
which some of them were
